The article discusses the Economic Report of the President, presented by Dr. Christina Romer, Chair of President Obama's Council of Economic Advisers. The report outlines the actions taken by the Obama administration to prevent the economy from falling into a depression and addresses long-term economic challenges. It focuses on rescuing the economy from the immediate crisis, rebalancing the economy towards greater investment and exports, and rebuilding the economy with quality healthcare, better education, clean energy, and innovation. The report is divided into three sections: an overview by the President, a comprehensive economic analysis by the Council of Economic Advisers, and key economic statistics. It covers topics such as financial rescue, international dimensions of the crisis, reducing the federal government budget deficit, and strengthening the foundation of the economy through healthcare reform, education and training, addressing climate change, and promoting productivity growth. The report includes original research and is the first to be published in color.